<div class="section">
<div class="sectiontitle">Latest News</div>

<p><span class="newsdate">January 25, 2009</span><br>
<a href="/glazedlists/glazedlists-1.8.0/">Glazed Lists 1.8.0</a> is a stable feature release suitable for production use.

<p><span class="newsdate">May 9, 2007</span><br>
<a href="http://publicobject.com/2007/05/glazed-lists-javaone-talk-friday-at.html">We're talking at JavaOne</a> on Friday afternoon. The tech session will start with an introduction to the APIs, then show off how they're used.

<p><span class="newsdate">August 10, 2006</span><br>
<a href="/glazedlists/glazedlists-1.7.0/">Glazed Lists 1.7.0</a> is an improvement release - with better event firing, autocomplete, and builds (Ant and Maven). It also fixes crucial performance bugs and adds a multimap feature.

<p><span class="newsdate">May 26, 2006</span><br>
<a href="/glazedlists/glazedlists-1.6.0/">Glazed Lists 1.6.0</a> introduces extensions. Extensions are rich bindings with other popular open source projects, which include
<a href="http://www.jfree.org/jfreechart/">JFreeChart</a>, <a href="http://www.jgoodies.com/freeware/forms/">JGoodies Forms</a>,
<a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/ktable">KTable</a>, <a href="http://nachocalendar.sourceforge.net">NachoCalendar</a> and
<a href="http://swinglabs.org/index.jsp">SwingLabs</a>. It also introduces the ability to decorate the standard Swing JComboBox
component with autocompletion features just like the address bar in FireFox. Finally, the underpinnings of ListEventAssembler were
refactored to increase the overall performance of Glazed Lists pipelines.

<p><span class="newsdate">December 21, 2005</span><br>
<a href="/glazedlists/glazedlists-1.5.0/">Glazed Lists 1.5.0</a> - adds support for Java 1.5 Generics while maintaining source compatibility with Java 1.4. It also adds two new list transformations, GroupingList and FunctionList.</p>

</div>

<p>For more in-depth information, browse the <a href="https://glazedlists.dev.java.net/servlets/BrowseList?listName=users">latest postings</a> on our mailing list.





